\subsubsection{Soil parameters}
We retrieved the required soil parameters from HiHydroSoil \citep{}; a composite dataset of soil hydraulic properties derived from global and regional soil information. Specifically, we retrieved values of the resisdual water content, the water content at field capacity, wilting point and saturation point at the native resolution of 30 arcseconds and aggregated to the model resolution. All variables were retrieved for two soil layers.

\subsubsection{Surface-water routing parameters}
We derived operational rules for the Gandak barrage from the monthly releases specified in the original agreement between India and Nepal \citep{}. We assume the storage pond immediately upstream of the barrage is steady-state; hence we assume that discharge immediately upstream of the barrage must be divided between the east and west canal branches and the main river downstream of the barrage. [Further explanation from Chris Jackson].

